HV11_011,Cash reserves,Barreserve,"Cash in vault and balances held with central banks (Deutsche Bundesbank, ECB). Includes notes and coins in domestic and foreign currency, credit balances on current accounts with the central bank, and postal giro balances. Reported at nominal value. Foreign currency amounts converted at the ECB reference rate on the reporting date."
HV11_021,Treasury bills,Schatzwechsel und unverzinsliche Schatzanweisungen,"Short-term debt instruments issued by central governments and similar public-sector entities, eligible for refinancing with central banks. Original maturity up to and including one year. Includes both interest-bearing treasury bills and non-interest-bearing treasury discount paper."
HV11_031,Other public-sector debt instruments,Schuldtitel oeffentlicher Stellen,"Debt instruments issued by central, regional and local governments and other public-sector entities, excluding treasury bills reported under HV11_021. Includes longer-dated bonds and notes of public authorities accepted as collateral for central bank refinancing operations."
HV11_061,Loans and advances to banks (MFIs),Forderungen an Kreditinstitute,"All claims on monetary financial institutions (credit institutions and money market funds resident in Germany and other EU member states). Includes overnight money (call money), time deposits placed, loans granted, and claims from genuine sale and repurchase transactions where the reporting institution acts as buyer (transferee). Broken down by maturity (on demand; up to 1 year; 1–5 years; over 5 years) and by domestic vs. foreign MFIs in Annex A1."
HV11_071,Loans and advances to non-banks (non-MFIs),Forderungen an Kunden,"All claims on non-MFI customers — enterprises, households, general government and non-profit institutions, whether domestic or foreign. Covers overdraft facilities, revolving loans, instalment loans, mortgage loans, consumer credit, municipal loans and other lending. Securitised loans that remain on the balance sheet (on-balance true sale) are included. Originally agreed maturity governs classification. Further broken down by sector, maturity, type of loan, collateral and interest rate adjustment in Annexes B1–B7."
HV11_080,Debt instruments,Schuldverschreibungen und andere festverzinsliche Wertpapiere,"Bonds, notes and other fixed-income securities held for own account, regardless of issuer (public authorities, credit institutions, other corporates). Includes Pfandbriefe, public-sector Pfandbriefe, eurobonds and other negotiable debt instruments with fixed or variable coupon. Reported at book value. Short sales of securities not held on the balance sheet result in negative amounts. Breakdown by issuer sector in Annex E1."
HV11_090,Shares and other variable-yield securities,Aktien und andere nicht festverzinsliche Wertpapiere,"Shares and other equity instruments, investment fund units (including money market fund units) and other variable-yield securities held for own account. Excludes participations and shares in affiliated enterprises, which are reported separately. Reported at book value. Short sales result in negative values. Breakdown by type in Annex E2."
HV11_100,Participations,Beteiligungen,"Equity interests in other enterprises where the reporting institution holds a durable interest (typically 20% or more of voting rights) without the enterprise being a controlled subsidiary. Includes interests in associated companies and joint ventures. Reported at acquisition cost adjusted for impairment or revaluations in accordance with the applicable accounting framework."
HV11_110,Shares in affiliated enterprises,Anteile an verbundenen Unternehmen,"Equity interests in subsidiaries and other affiliated enterprises where the reporting institution exercises controlling influence (typically more than 50% of voting rights or equivalent control). Includes domestic and foreign subsidiaries. Reported at book value in accordance with HGB section 271 or IFRS 10 definition of control."
HV11_120,Trust assets,Treuhandvermoegen,"Assets held by the reporting institution in its own name but on behalf of third parties (fiduciary capacity). The beneficial owner is a third party; the reporting institution carries no credit risk. Reported gross on the asset side, matched by the corresponding trust liabilities (HV21_240) on the liability side. Includes fiduciary loans, trust securities and other assets managed as trustee."
HV11_130,Equalisation claims against public authorities,Ausgleichsforderungen gegen oeffentliche Hand,"Fixed-interest claims on federal and state governments arising from the Deutsche Mark currency reform of 1948. Granted to credit institutions as compensation for balance sheet losses incurred in the post-war currency conversion. Largely of historical significance; reduced by scheduled redemption over decades."
HV11_140,Intangible assets,Immaterielle Anlagewerte,"Non-physical non-current assets including purchased software, licences, patents, trademarks, customer relationships and goodwill from business combinations. Under HGB only purchased intangibles are capitalised (section 248 HGB). Under IFRS, internally generated intangibles meeting IAS 38 recognition criteria are also included. Reported at cost less accumulated amortisation and any impairment losses."
HV11_150,Property and equipment,Sachanlagen,"Tangible non-current assets owned and used in operations, including land and buildings, leasehold improvements, office furniture, IT hardware and vehicles. Reported at cost less accumulated depreciation and impairment. Right-of-use assets recognised under IFRS 16 lease arrangements are also included here where applicable."
HV11_160,Unpaid contributions to subscribed capital,Ausstehende Einlagen auf gezeichnetes Kapital,"Amounts subscribed by shareholders to the capital of the reporting institution that have been called but not yet paid in cash. Recorded as an asset when the payment obligation has been formally established. Partly offset against the gross subscribed capital on the liabilities side in some balance sheet presentations."
HV11_170,Other assets,Sonstige Vermoegensgegenstände,"Catch-all position for all assets not classifiable under the preceding items. Includes positive fair values of derivative financial instruments held in the trading portfolio, settlement accounts, sundry debtors, precious metals held for own account, dividend receivables, and miscellaneous other claims. Also captures currency conversion differences (rounding items) on the asset side where no dedicated item exists. See HV21_250 on the liabilities side for the corresponding catch-all."
HV11_175,Tax receivables,Steuererstattungsansprueche,"Current tax receivables representing refund claims against tax authorities arising from overpayments or advance tax payments (Körperschaftsteuer, Gewerbesteuer). Under IFRS, deferred tax assets (IAS 12) arising from deductible temporary differences and unused tax losses are also included here, to the extent it is probable that future taxable profits will be available."
HV11_176,Prepaid expenses and accrued income,Rechnungsabgrenzungsposten Aktiva,"Expenditures paid before the reporting date but attributable to a future accounting period (prepaid expenses), and income earned before the reporting date but not yet received in cash (accrued income). Includes accrued interest on loans and securities portfolios, prepaid insurance premiums, prepaid rent and loan origination fees to be amortised. Reported at nominal value."
HV21_210,Liabilities to banks (MFIs),Verbindlichkeiten gegenueber Kreditinstituten,"All amounts owed to monetary financial institutions, including overnight deposits received (call money), time deposits taken, loans borrowed, and liabilities from genuine sale and repurchase transactions where the reporting institution acts as seller (transferor). The transferor must show the amount received as a liability to the transferee (HV21_210) while keeping the transferred assets on its balance sheet. Broken down by maturity and domestic/foreign in Annex A2."
HV21_220,Other liabilities to non-banks (non-MFIs),Andere Verbindlichkeiten gegenueber Kunden (Nicht-MFI),"Deposits and other amounts owed to non-MFI customers (enterprises, households, general government, non-profit institutions), excluding savings deposits reported under HV21_222. Covers demand deposits (current accounts, sight deposits), time deposits and notice deposits that do not qualify as savings deposits. Further broken down by sector, maturity and geographic area in Annexes C1–C5."
HV21_222,Savings deposits,Spareinlagen,"Deposits qualifying as Spareinlagen under German banking law: not intended for payment purposes, typically documented by a savings passbook or equivalent instrument, with a minimum statutory notice period of three months. Includes savings deposits with agreed notice periods exceeding three months and fixed-term savings instruments. Broken down by type and maturity in Annexes D1–D2."
HV21_230,Securitised liabilities,Verbriefte Verbindlichkeiten,"Liabilities in the form of transferable debt securities issued by the reporting institution, including mortgage bonds (Pfandbriefe), public-sector Pfandbriefe, senior unsecured bonds, money market paper and certificates of deposit traded on financial markets. Excludes subordinated instruments (reported under HV21_300). Reported at issuance proceeds or amortised cost. Broken down by type and maturity in Annexes E4/E5 and F1/F2."
HV21_240,Trust liabilities,Treuhandverbindlichkeiten,"Liabilities corresponding to trust assets held on the asset side (HV11_120). These represent the reporting institution's obligation to the beneficial owners of assets held in a fiduciary capacity. Always reported at the same amount as the corresponding trust assets. No credit risk is borne by the reporting institution on these positions."
HV21_250,Other liabilities,Sonstige Verbindlichkeiten,"Catch-all position for all liabilities not classifiable under other items. Includes negative fair values of derivative financial instruments in the trading portfolio, lease liabilities (IFRS 16), trade payables, social security and payroll obligations, and miscellaneous other creditors. Currency conversion differences on the liabilities side are also recorded here. Corresponds to HV11_170 on the asset side."
HV21_260,Deferred income,Rechnungsabgrenzungsposten Passiva,"Income received before the reporting date but attributable to a future accounting period (deferred income), and expenditure attributable to a past period but not yet paid (accrued liabilities). Includes accrued interest payable on deposits and securities issued, deferred loan origination fees received from borrowers, and prepaid service fees. Reported at nominal value."
HV21_270,Provisions,Rueckstellungen,"Liabilities of uncertain timing or amount recognised for obligations from past events where an outflow of resources is probable. Includes provisions for pensions and similar post-employment benefits, tax provisions, provisions for contingent liabilities (guarantees, irrevocable lending commitments), provisions for restructuring and other uncertain obligations. Recognised in accordance with HGB section 249 or IAS 37."
HV21_280,Tax liabilities,Steuerverbindlichkeiten,"Current tax liabilities representing amounts owed to tax authorities including corporate income tax (Koerperschaftsteuer), solidarity surcharge, and trade tax (Gewerbesteuer). Under IFRS, deferred tax liabilities (IAS 12) arising from taxable temporary differences — where the tax base of an asset exceeds its carrying amount or the carrying amount of a liability exceeds its tax base — are also included."
HV21_300,Subordinated liabilities,Nachrangige Verbindlichkeiten,"Debt instruments whose holders rank after all other creditors in insolvency or liquidation (contractually subordinated). Includes subordinated bonds, subordinated term loans and similar instruments qualifying as Tier 2 regulatory capital under the Capital Requirements Regulation (CRR/EU 575/2013). The subordinated ranking must be explicitly stipulated in the contractual documentation. Reported separately due to loss-absorbing capacity."
HV21_310,Participation rights capital,Genussrechtskapital,"Capital raised through the issuance of profit participation rights (Genussscheine or Genussrechte). Holders receive a contractual share in profits and typically rank ahead of shareholders but behind other creditors in liquidation. Does not convey voting rights. Qualifies as Tier 2 regulatory capital if it meets minimum maturity, subordination and loss-participation conditions. Broadly comparable to Additional Tier 1 instruments in IFRS terminology."
HV21_320,Fund for general banking risks,Fonds fuer allgemeine Bankrisiken,"A special precautionary reserve created exclusively under section 340g HGB by German credit institutions to cover general banking risks not captured by specific provisions or regulatory capital. Allocated from annual profits at management's discretion. Treated as an exception to the ledger-level principle — reported at book level rather than individual ledger entry level, as explicitly stated in HV21_300 (exception items HV21_300, HV21_310 and HV22_339)."
HV21_325,Capital and reserves,Eigenkapital,"Residual interest of shareholders after deducting all liabilities. Comprises: subscribed capital (Gezeichnetes Kapital); capital reserve (Kapitalruecklage); revenue reserves including statutory reserve, reserve for own shares, and other revenue reserves (Gewinnruecklagen); and the balance sheet profit or loss for the current period (Bilanzgewinn/-verlust). Under IFRS also includes OCI reserves (FVOCI revaluation reserve, cash flow hedge reserve, foreign currency translation reserve) and non-controlling interests."
